The documented origin and history of data - where it came from, who created it, and when. Data provenance answers the question "where did this number come from?" by providing a traceable path back to the original source.

Think of it as a birth certificate for your data. When the CEO questions why the dashboard shows different numbers than the ERP, provenance lets you trace each figure back to the specific application screen where someone entered it.

Not to be confused with [[Data Lineage]], which tracks transformations rather than origins.